gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://www.youtube.com/@NicoleCoenen</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/A30HG2h</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ilikespreadsheets]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Japanese dress as famous paintings in this Halloween parade</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/WKHMOs8</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/C0y8nyT.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/WKHMOs8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GinglaBambino]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Wasn’t expecting to see this when I came home from work…</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/6GBlk8N</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/CgoTDvq.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>When I picked up my new orange foster kitten this afternoon he was shaking uncontrollably in the carrier. The introduction to my other foster kittens Freddy and Jason went really well, but I had no idea what was going to happen during the four hours I had to go back to work. But when I came into the kitten room things were better than I could have hoped! Suffice to say Jason has fully accepted the newbie, and Freddy seems fine with the situation as well. Yay!!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/6GBlk8N</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[KittensForDays]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>You shall not pass, without an updoot</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Ykke495</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Bn6Pnn0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Ykke495</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ToastySnek]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Totó likes hugs</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/7WZUnwj</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://